      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just such a heavy way to exist. every morning i wake up and it's like i'm dragging this corpse around. i look at people living their lives, laughing and planning for the future, and it feels like they're a different species. i don't see a way back to being \"real.\" it feels like there's nothing left to save, just an empty house where someone used to live.",
